reviews.review_text:
This was my 1st show Thanks for this fine recording! You made my day when I downloaded this! 

Can it be? Almost 39 years ago that Joanne, Gary & I drove up from DC and found our way into Baltimore, full of anticipation. It was the 1st show for all of us. We'd cut our teeth on "Skull & Roses", five years before, then  "Europe '72" and all the studio albums but had no access to live recordings. We didn't know quite what for, but we felt ready! 

What a show - they did NOT disappoint. Bobby was right - the Baltimore Civic Center was an "old barn" but the sound was dialed right in pretty quickly. By the time Donna was singing "Passenger", it was right and she sounded beautiful. I really didn't understand why some heads were hating on her. 

This Baltimore show, for me, outshines the Cornell show everyone was raving about going in and that was how one head was talking on the way out - that  they had rocked OUT in Richmond the night before, but Baltimore was in the Crown Jewels. The  Terrapin Station > Estimated Prophet > Eyes Of The World > Not Fade Away > Goin' Down the Road Feeling Bad > Around and Around just blew us away, we were hoping they'd "play one song into another, how they do" - I loved it  .. THANKS AGAIN!
Made my day! What a pleasure to hear this show.

First show- and what a night First show - my roommate at Towson U took me down to the show- and boy after twenty minutes on the lot, a couple of Fast Eddie's finest and the opening ten notes of TMNS i was hooked- been on the bus ever since.
great show, and what a blessing to have hopped up on the bus in Spring 77 followed up by the September trip to Englishtown for NRPS/MT/GD that for me was one of the great experiences of my life.
